This contributes to the following Country Programme result: All Namibian children from ages 0â€“10 years have improved access to quality and equitable maternal, neonatal and child health, education, child protection, Early Child Development (ECD), civil registration, nutrition and Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) services by 2023.

description.narrative: Through UNICEF support, 727,276 people were reached with COVID-19 messages, including 1; million;on COVID-19 vaccination. UNICEF partnership with InterTeam Swiss leveraged double the UNICEF budget for the ECD RightStart campaign to ensure year-round mass media coverage, reaching a radio listenership of 470,000 across 11 radio stations, a weekly newspaper readership of 40,000, and a website and social media reach of over 391,000. A total of 2,745 parents were capacitated with improved parenting skills, including identification of children with disabilities and linkages to services. Fewer communities than expected reached ODF status amid constrained triggering and follow-up due to COVID-19 restrictions.; | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:05/12/2021
